name: Simple Keto Zucchini Hash
author: Heather Petersen
summary: This recipe makes an amazing side dish. Flavorful and high in healthy fat, it is a great complement to a meat or other high-protein main dish. If you like the flavors of zucchini and chili powder and miss the texture of mashed potatoes, try this one.
ingredients: 4 small zucchini, grated and squeezed dry
1 teaspoon chili powder, or more to taste
directions: Combine zucchini with coconut oil and butter in a medium skillet over medium heat
Add Parmesan cheese, chili powder, salt, and cayenne pepper
Reduce heat to low and add eggs; stir quickly until fully mixed in
Increase heat back to medium and cook, stirring and flipping occasionally, until edges of the hash are lightly browned, about 15 minutes
